/backend
├── /config
│   ├── db.js               # Database connection logic
│   ├── env.js              # Environment variable setup
├── /controllers
│   ├── userController.js   # Controller for user-related logic
│   ├── authController.js   # Controller for authentication
├── /middleware
│   ├── authMiddleware.js   # Middleware for authorization
│   ├── errorHandler.js     # Global error handler
├── /models
│   ├── User.js             # User schema/model
│   ├── Post.js             # Post schema/model
├── /routes
│   ├── userRoutes.js       # Routes for user-related APIs
│   ├── authRoutes.js       # Routes for authentication APIs
├── /utils
│   ├── helpers.js          # Utility functions
│   ├── emailSender.js      # Helper for sending emails
├── app.js                  # Main Express application
├── server.js               # Server setup and listening
├── package.json            # Backend dependencies


Install Required Packages
Install Express, Mongoose (for MongoDB), and other necessary packages:
bash
npm install express mongoose dotenv nodemailer bcryptjs jsonwebtoken cors

express: Web framework for Node.js.
mongoose: MongoDB object modeling tool.
dotenv: Loads environment variables from a .env file.
nodemailer: For sending emails.
bcryptjs: For hashing passwords.
jsonwebtoken: For generating JWT tokens.
cors: To enable Cross-Origin Resource Sharing.